 <p>When you level up, you gain one level-up point, with the amount
 increasing by two every five levels. You may buy the following upgrades
 with level-up points:</p>
 <ul>
 <li>+5 to Health or speed, or +1 to an attacking or defending stat</li>
 <li>Increase a skill by 5% (no skill may be above 95%)</li>
 <li>One trait from any bracket available to you. Grade 1 abilities cost
 1 point. Grade 2 2 points, Grade 3 5 points, Grade 4 cost 8 points and
 Grade 5 cost 10 points</li>
 <li>One of your Pokemons available Abilities</li>
 </ul>
 <ol type="1">
 <li><p>You can learn new moves if available and may gain additional
 benefits, such as increasing one attribute or acquiring an extra
 ability.</p></li>
 <li><p>Your maximum Hit Points increase by your Health score. This
 increase is not retroactive, so it will not apply if your Health score
 is boosted through stat increases or evolution.</p></li>
 </ol>
 <p>Move Upgrades:</p>
 <ol start="3" type="1">
 <li>Move Upgrades are enhancements to specific Moves, making them more
 versatile or specialized. These are optional, and the Dungeon Master
 (DM) may choose not to include them. Each move can have only one Move
 Upgrade.</li>
 </ol>
 <h1 id="playing-the-game">Playing the Game</h1>
